<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>Trace Report — {{ investigation_id }}</title>
{% include "_styles.html.j2" %}
<style>
  /* Trace-report-specific overrides — internal forensic
     worksheet aesthetic. Lighter on chrome, more density
     than the customer-facing freeze letter. */
  .internal-stamp {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-left: 0.6em;
    padding: 2px 8px;
    border: 1px solid var(--confidential);
    color: var(--confidential);
    font-size: var(--type-tiny);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    vertical-align: middle;
  }
  .stat-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 0.4em 1.2em;
    margin: var(--space-md) 0 var(--space-lg);
    padding: 0.8em 1em;
    background: var(--paper-tint);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--gold-accent);
  }
  .stat-grid > div {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    font-size: var(--type-small);
  }
  .stat-grid dt { color: var(--ink-quiet); font-weight: 500; }
  .stat-grid dd { font-weight: 600; color: var(--ink); margin: 0; }
  .freeze-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 1px 8px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    font-size: var(--type-tiny);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .freeze-badge.high   { background: #DCFCE7; color: #14532D; }
  .freeze-badge.medium { background: #FEF3C7; color: #5C2D0F; }
  .freeze-badge.low    { background: #FED7AA; color: #5C1F09; }
  .freeze-badge.none   { background: #F1F5F9; color: #475569; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<section class="cover">
  <div class="cover-letterhead">
    <div class="cover-wordmark">
      Recupero
      <span class="tagline">Investigation Services</span>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-letterhead-right">
      <div class="confidential">Internal Use Only</div>
      <div class="date">{{ generated_at }} UTC</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="cover-title-block">
    <div class="cover-eyebrow">Forensic Worksheet · Wallet Trace Report</div>
    <h1>Trace Report
      <span class="internal-stamp">Internal Use Only</span>
    </h1>
    <p class="cover-subtitle">
      Data-only summary of on-chain trace findings.
      {% if label %}Label: <strong>{{ label }}</strong>.{% endif %}
      Not for external distribution — this artifact contains raw
      investigative data without the case narrative or
      customer-facing prose. For an externally-shareable summary,
      see the freeze-request and LE-handoff deliverables.
    </p>
    <div class="cover-rule"></div>
  </div>

  <dl class="cover-meta">
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Investigation ID</dt>
      <dd class="mono">{{ investigation_id }}</dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Traced Wallet</dt>
      <dd>{% if wallet_explorer_url %}<a class="mono" href="{{ wallet_explorer_url|safe_url }}">{{ wallet_address }}</a>{% else %}<span class="mono">{{ wallet_address }}</span>{% endif %}</dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Chain</dt>
      <dd>{{ chain }}</dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Run Timestamp</dt>
      <dd>{{ generated_at }} UTC</dd>
    </div>
    {% if label %}
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Label</dt>
      <dd>{{ label }}</dd>
    </div>
    {% endif %}
  </dl>
</section>

<h2>1. Trace Summary</h2>
{# v0.7.4: lead with gross perpetrator-controlled holdings as the
   headline number when present. This is the scoping figure a
   downstream lawyer / law-enforcement analyst needs first —
   "what's the actionable footprint at perpetrator-controlled
   addresses," not "what's the attribution share of victim funds."
   Falls back to the attribution-only view when the brief didn't
   compute the field (older briefs, wallet-trace runs without an
   emit_brief stage). #}
{% if stats.total_perpetrator_holdings_usd %}
<div class="headline-figure">
  <div class="headline-figure-label">Perpetrator-controlled holdings</div>
  <div class="headline-figure-value">{{ stats.total_perpetrator_holdings_usd }}</div>
  <div class="headline-figure-note">
    Gross current balance across all identified perpetrator-controlled
    destinations (the consolidation hub and downstream addresses).
    This is the scoping number for seizure / freeze action — distinct
    from the attribution-share figure below, which is what was provably
    traced from the victim's wallet.
  </div>
</div>
{% endif %}
<dl class="stat-grid">
  {# JACOB-EYEBALL: surface TOTAL_LOSS_USD ("what was stolen
     from the victim") as the lead figure. Operators reading the
     trace report shouldn't have to compute this from FREEZABLE
     deltas — it's the case's headline number. #}
  {% if stats.total_loss_usd %}
  <div>
    <dt>Total drained from victim</dt>
    <dd>{{ stats.total_loss_usd }}</dd>
  </div>
  {% endif %}
  <div><dt>Total transfers analyzed</dt><dd>{{ stats.total_transfers }}</dd></div>
  <div><dt>Max depth reached</dt><dd>{{ stats.max_depth_reached }}</dd></div>
  <div>
    <dt>Attributable flow value (USD)</dt>
    <dd>{{ stats.total_flow_usd }}</dd>
  </div>
  <div><dt>Destinations identified</dt><dd>{{ stats.destinations_count }}</dd></div>
  <div><dt>Trace started</dt><dd class="mono">{{ stats.trace_started_at }}</dd></div>
  <div><dt>Trace completed</dt><dd class="mono">{{ stats.trace_completed_at }}</dd></div>
</dl>

<h2>2. Destination Addresses</h2>
{% if destinations %}
<p class="small">
  Every distinct destination wallet identified by the trace, with
  current holdings priced at fetch time. Click any address to open
  it on the chain explorer.
  Positions flagged <strong>UNRECOVERABLE</strong> (DAI / USDS via
  Sky Protocol) have no admin freeze pathway — the issuer does not
  retain the power to freeze these holdings, so they are listed
  here for asset-seizure evidence only, not for issuer outreach.
</p>
<table class="evidence">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Address</th>
      <th>Role / Label</th>
      <th>Asset</th>
      <th>Balance</th>
      <th>USD Value</th>
      <th>Freeze Path</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    {% for d in destinations %}
    <tr>
      <td class="mono">{% if d.explorer_url %}<a href="{{ d.explorer_url|safe_url }}">{{ d.address_short }}</a>{% else %}<span>{{ d.address_short }}</span>{% endif %}</td>
      <td>{{ d.role }}{% if d.label %}<br/><span class="small secondary">{{ d.label }}</span>{% endif %}</td>
      <td>{{ d.symbol or '—' }}</td>
      <td class="mono">{{ d.balance_human or '—' }}</td>
      <td class="amount">{{ d.usd_value_human or '—' }}</td>
      <td>
        {% if d.is_unrecoverable %}
        <span class="label-pill" style="color:#6B7280; font-weight:600;">UNRECOVERABLE</span>
        <br/><span class="small secondary">Sky Protocol — no admin freeze pathway</span>
        {% else %}
        <span class="small secondary">—</span>
        {% endif %}
      </td>
    </tr>
    {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>
{% else %}
<p>No destination addresses identified beyond the seed wallet.</p>
{% endif %}

<h2>3. Freeze Potential</h2>
{% if freezable_rows %}
<p class="small">
  Destinations holding assets the issuer can freeze. Capability
  taxonomy: <strong>HIGH</strong> (issuer has direct freeze
  authority), <strong>MEDIUM</strong> (issuer can freeze with some
  friction), <strong>LOW</strong> (technically possible but
  unprecedented or contested), <strong>NOT FREEZABLE</strong>
  (staking/permissionless contract — issuer has no power).
</p>
<table class="evidence">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Address</th>
      <th>Asset</th>
      <th>Balance</th>
      <th>USD Value</th>
      <th>Evidence</th>
      <th>Issuer</th>
      <th>Freezability</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    {% for f in freezable_rows %}
    <tr>
      <td class="mono">{% if f.explorer_url %}<a href="{{ f.explorer_url|safe_url }}">{{ f.address_short }}</a>{% else %}<span>{{ f.address_short }}</span>{% endif %}</td>
      <td>{{ f.symbol }}</td>
      <td class="mono">{{ f.amount }}</td>
      <td class="amount">{{ f.usd }}</td>
      <td>
        {# v0.16.2 (audit fix #6): evidence column tells the operator
           whether the USD figure is a confirmed current balance or
           a historical-receipt sum from the trace. Critical for
           V-CFI01-shape cases where dormant detection failed and
           the historical synthesizer fired. #}
        {% if f.evidence_type == "historical_inflow" %}
        <span class="evidence-pill historical">historical receipt</span>
        {% else %}
        <span class="evidence-pill current">current balance</span>
        {% endif %}
      </td>
      <td>{{ f.issuer }}</td>
      <td>
        <span class="freeze-badge {{ f.capability_class }}">
          {{ f.capability }}
        </span>
      </td>
    </tr>
    {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>
{% else %}
<p>No destinations identified holding freezable assets. The
trace's terminal wallets either hold non-freezable assets (native
gas tokens, non-stablecoin tokens with no issuer-level controls)
or are at exchanges / mixers / bridges that require a different
recovery path (subpoena, mixer report, bridge operator
notification).</p>
{% endif %}

{# v0.9.x sections — cross-chain handoffs, entity clusters,
   risk assessment. Always rendered with section headers
   (even when empty) because "no findings detected" is a useful
   confirmation for a government / law-enforcement reader that
   the analysis was performed. #}

<h2>4. Cross-Chain Handoffs</h2>
{% if cross_chain_handoffs %}
<p class="small">
  Funds bridged off the source chain via a known cross-chain
  bridge. The trace cannot follow money past a bridge contract
  (different chain, different state machine), but each handoff
  is recorded with the destination-chain candidates and a
  follow-up URL so a downstream investigator can continue the
  trace on the destination chain.
</p>
<table class="evidence">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Time</th>
      <th>Bridge</th>
      <th>Source address</th>
      <th>Amount</th>
      <th>Token</th>
      <th>Destination candidates</th>
      <th>Follow-up</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    {% for h in cross_chain_handoffs %}
    <tr>
      <td class="small">{{ h.block_time }}</td>
      <td>{{ h.bridge_name }}<br/><span class="small secondary">{{ h.bridge_protocol }}</span></td>
      {# v0.32.1 (Jacob cross-cutting audit §3.1): canonical short_address filter. #}
      <td class="mono">{% if h.tx_explorer_url %}<a href="{{ h.tx_explorer_url|safe_url }}">{{ h.source_address | short_address(prefix=10, suffix=0) }}</a>{% else %}<span>{{ h.source_address | short_address(prefix=10, suffix=0) }}</span>{% endif %}</td>
      <td class="amount">{{ h.amount_usd or h.amount_decimal }}</td>
      <td>{{ h.token_symbol }}</td>
      <td class="small">{{ h.destination_chain_candidates | join(', ') if h.destination_chain_candidates else '(see bridge explorer)' }}</td>
      <td class="small">
        {% if h.follow_up_url %}<a href="{{ h.follow_up_url|safe_url }}">{{ h.follow_up_url }}</a>{% else %}—{% endif %}
      </td>
    </tr>
    {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>
<p class="small">
  <strong>Investigator note format:</strong> each entry contains
  a one-line investigator action item embedded in the brief's
  JSON (see <span class="mono">cross_chain_handoffs[].investigator_note</span>
  in the corresponding <span class="mono">freeze_brief.json</span>).
</p>
{% else %}
<p>No cross-chain handoffs detected. The trace did not observe
   transfers to any known bridge contract.</p>
{% endif %}

<h2>5. Entity Clusters</h2>
{% if entity_clusters and entity_clusters.clusters %}
<p class="small">
  Addresses that appear to belong to the same actor, grouped via
  on-chain behavioral signals: shared funding source (H1),
  shared withdrawal target (H2), and round-number self-funding
  (H3). Each cluster carries evidence so the investigator can
  verify the heuristic fired correctly.
</p>
{% for cluster in entity_clusters.clusters %}
<div class="cluster-card">
  <h3 style="margin-top:1.2em;">{{ cluster.cluster_id }} — {{ cluster.size }} addresses
    {% if cluster.total_balance_usd %}({{ cluster.total_balance_usd }} total){% endif %}</h3>
  <p class="small"><strong>Addresses:</strong></p>
  <ul class="address-list">
    {% for addr in cluster.addresses %}
    <li class="mono">{{ addr }}</li>
    {% endfor %}
  </ul>
  <p class="small"><strong>Clustering evidence:</strong></p>
  <ul class="evidence-list">
    {% for ev in cluster.evidence %}
    <li>
      <strong>{{ ev.heuristic }}</strong>
      ({{ ev.confidence }} confidence):
      {{ ev.details }}
      {# v0.32.1 (Jacob cross-cutting audit §3.1): canonical short_address filter. #}
      {% if ev.related_address %}— via <span class="mono">{{ ev.related_address | short_address(prefix=14, suffix=0) }}</span>{% endif %}
    </li>
    {% endfor %}
  </ul>
</div>
{% endfor %}
{% else %}
<p>No entity clusters detected. The trace's addresses either
   lacked behavioral signals (shared funding source within 24h,
   shared withdrawal target within 12h) or each address operated
   independently in this case.</p>
{% endif %}

<h2>6. Risk Assessment</h2>
{% if risk_assessment and risk_assessment.summary is defined and risk_assessment.summary and risk_assessment.summary.addresses_assessed > 0 %}
<div class="risk-summary">
  <div class="risk-summary-stat">
    <div class="risk-summary-label">Addresses assessed</div>
    <div class="risk-summary-value">{{ risk_assessment.summary.addresses_assessed }}</div>
  </div>
  <div class="risk-summary-stat">
    <div class="risk-summary-label">OFAC-exposed</div>
    <div class="risk-summary-value">{{ risk_assessment.summary.ofac_exposed_count }}</div>
  </div>
  <div class="risk-summary-stat">
    <div class="risk-summary-label">Mixer-exposed</div>
    <div class="risk-summary-value">{{ risk_assessment.summary.mixer_exposed_count }}</div>
  </div>
  <div class="risk-summary-stat">
    <div class="risk-summary-label">Highest score</div>
    <div class="risk-summary-value">{{ risk_assessment.summary.highest_score }}</div>
  </div>
</div>
{% if risk_assessment.summary.ofac_exposed_count > 0 %}
<p class="risk-warning">
  <strong>SANCTIONED EXPOSURE DETECTED.</strong> One or more
  addresses in this case had direct transactions with OFAC SDN
  List entries. For U.S. persons this elevates the case to
  federal jurisdiction (Treasury / OFAC reporting obligations
  may apply). See per-address detail below.
</p>
{% endif %}
<table class="evidence">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Address</th>
      <th>Score</th>
      <th>Verdict</th>
      <th>Exposures</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    {% for addr, data in (risk_assessment.addresses or {}).items() %}
    <tr>
      {# v0.32.1 (Jacob cross-cutting audit §3.1): canonical short_address filter. #}
      <td class="mono">{{ addr | short_address(prefix=14, suffix=0) }}</td>
      <td class="amount">{{ data.score }}</td>
      <td>{{ data.verdict }}</td>
      <td class="small">
        {% for exp in data.exposures %}
        <div>
          {{ exp.direction }} {{ exp.total_usd }} —
          {{ exp.counterparty_name }}
          ({{ exp.risk_category }}, sev {{ exp.severity }})
        </div>
        {% endfor %}
      </td>
    </tr>
    {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>
{% else %}
<p>No high-risk exposures detected. The trace's addresses had
   no direct transactions with OFAC SDN List entries, sanctioned
   mixers, known darknet markets, or documented scam/drainer
   services.</p>
<p class="small"><em>This is a positive finding for the case — the
   perpetrator's operational footprint avoided
   immediately-flagged infrastructure. Investigators should still
   look for indirect / multi-hop exposure beyond what's surfaced
   here (this v0.9.x assessment is direct-counterparty only).</em></p>
{% endif %}

<h2>7. Flow Visualization</h2>
{% if flow_filename %}
<p class="attachment-note">
  The complete fund-flow diagram is provided as a separate SVG
  attachment (<span class="mono">{{ flow_filename }}</span>)
  accompanying this report. Open in any modern browser to inspect
  at full resolution; each wallet node links directly to its
  on-chain explorer record.
</p>
{% else %}
<p>Flow diagram unavailable for this trace.</p>
{% endif %}

{% if demix_leads %}
<h2>8. Mixer-Demixing Leads</h2>
<p class="small"><em>Probabilistic LEADS only &mdash; never proof. A mixer
   cryptographically severs the deposit&harr;withdrawal link; the rows below
   are same-pool withdrawals that share a behavioral signal (address reuse /
   relayer / gas / FIFO timing) with a mixer deposit observed in this trace.
   They are investigative leads for manual review (e.g. a subpoena to the
   relayer, or a watch on the withdrawal address), NEVER a followed
   destination, and are reported at LOW confidence.</em></p>
{% for dep in demix_leads.deposits %}
<p class="small mono">Pool / deposit: {{ dep.key }}</p>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Candidate withdrawal address</th>
      <th>Pool</th>
      <th>Signals</th>
      <th>Score</th>
      <th>Confidence</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
  {% for ld in dep.leads %}
    <tr>
      <td class="mono">{{ ld.withdrawal_address }}</td>
      <td>{{ ld.pool }}</td>
      <td>{{ ld.signals | join(', ') }}</td>
      <td>{{ ld.score }}</td>
      <td>{{ ld.confidence }}</td>
    </tr>
  {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

{% if burn_sinks %}
<h2>9. Burned / Provably-Destroyed Funds</h2>
<p class="small"><em>Funds sent to a provably-unspendable address &mdash; the
   zero address, a canonical <span class="mono">0xdEaD</span> burn, or a
   chain incinerator. No private key exists, so these are UNRECOVERABLE by
   construction; they are listed so the recoverable total is not overstated.
   (Sanctioned mixer pools are reported as mixer terminals, not burns.)</em></p>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Burn address</th>
      <th>Type</th>
      <th>Chain</th>
      <th>Transfers</th>
      <th>Value</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
  {% for b in burn_sinks %}
    <tr>
      <td class="mono">{{ b.address }}</td>
      <td>{{ b.burn_type }}</td>
      <td>{{ b.chain }}</td>
      <td>{{ b.count }}</td>
      <td>{{ b.total_usd }}</td>
    </tr>
  {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>
{% endif %}

{% if nft_flows %}
<h2>10. Observed NFT Transfers</h2>
<p class="small"><em>On-chain ERC-721 / ERC-1155 transfers involving traced
   wallets &mdash; OBSERVATIONS only. NFT-sale laundering and mint-and-flip
   moves are listed so they do not silently vanish from the case record; no
   USD value is claimed unless the data provider supplied one, NFT recipients
   are NOT followed, and the recoverable total is unchanged. Matching an NFT
   exit to its marketplace-sale proceeds requires separate manual review.</em></p>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Traced wallet</th>
      <th>Dir</th>
      <th>Counterparty</th>
      <th>Collection / contract</th>
      <th>Token</th>
      <th>Std</th>
      <th>Qty</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
  {% for f in nft_flows.flows %}
    <tr>
      <td class="mono">{{ f.traced_wallet | short_address(prefix=10, suffix=4) }}</td>
      <td>{{ f.direction }}</td>
      <td class="mono">{{ f.counterparty | short_address(prefix=10, suffix=4) }}</td>
      <td>{% if f.collection_name %}{{ f.collection_name }}<br/>{% endif %}<span class="mono small">{{ f.contract_address | short_address(prefix=10, suffix=4) }}</span></td>
      <td class="mono">#{{ f.token_id | truncate(16, True, '…') }}</td>
      <td>{{ f.token_standard }}</td>
      <td>{{ f.value_count }}</td>
    </tr>
  {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>
{% endif %}

{% if lp_leads %}
<h2>11. LP Park-and-Withdraw Leads (Uniswap V3)</h2>
<p class="small"><em>A traced wallet deposited value into a Uniswap V3
   position; the rows below are the later <span class="mono">Collect</span>
   exits on the <strong>same position tokenId</strong> &mdash; protocol
   identity, so the position link is HIGH confidence. Actor attribution is
   HIGH only when the exit recipient IS the parking wallet; otherwise MEDIUM
   (the position NFT may have changed hands &mdash; review the NFT ownership
   trail). Amounts are raw per-pool-token units (never priced here); leads
   are for review, NEVER a followed destination, and the recoverable total
   is unchanged.</em></p>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Parking wallet</th>
      <th>Position</th>
      <th>Exit recipient</th>
      <th>Same owner</th>
      <th>Position link</th>
      <th>Actor attribution</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
  {% for ld in lp_leads.leads %}
    <tr>
      <td class="mono">{{ ld.parker | short_address(prefix=10, suffix=4) }}</td>
      <td class="mono">#{{ ld.position_token_id }}</td>
      <td class="mono">{{ ld.exit_recipient | short_address(prefix=10, suffix=4) }}</td>
      <td>{{ "yes" if ld.recipient_is_parker else "no" }}</td>
      <td>{{ ld.position_link_confidence }}</td>
      <td>{{ ld.actor_attribution_confidence }}</td>
    </tr>
  {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>
{% endif %}

{% if lending_leads %}
<h2>12. Lending Cross-Address Withdrawals (Aave V3 / Compound III)</h2>
<p class="small"><em>A traced wallet withdrew supplied funds from a lending
   protocol (Aave V3 or Compound III / Comet) <strong>directly to a different
   address</strong> &mdash; an exit sent by the protocol contract and therefore
   invisible to outflow enumeration. Both the initiating wallet and the exit
   recipient are protocol-stamped indexed topics on the
   <span class="mono">Withdraw</span> event (HIGH confidence; Comet is queried
   only against pinned, verified markets). Withdrawals back to the traced
   wallet itself are not listed (those funds re-enter normal tracing). Amounts
   are raw reserve / base-asset units; leads are for review, NEVER a followed
   destination, and the recoverable total is unchanged.</em></p>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Traced wallet (user)</th>
      <th>Exit recipient</th>
      <th>Reserve</th>
      <th>Amount (raw)</th>
      <th>Confidence</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
  {% for ld in lending_leads.leads %}
    <tr>
      <td class="mono">{{ ld.user | short_address(prefix=10, suffix=4) }}</td>
      <td class="mono">{{ ld.exit_recipient | short_address(prefix=10, suffix=4) }}</td>
      <td class="mono">{{ ld.reserve | short_address(prefix=10, suffix=4) }}</td>
      <td class="mono">{{ ld.amount_raw }}</td>
      <td>{{ ld.confidence }}</td>
    </tr>
  {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>
{% endif %}

{% if vault_leads %}
<h2>13. ERC-4626 Vault Cross-Address Withdrawals</h2>
<p class="small"><em>A traced wallet redeemed ERC-4626 vault shares
   (Morpho / Yearn / Spark / any compliant vault) with the underlying assets
   sent to a <strong>different receiver</strong> &mdash; an exit emitted by
   the vault, invisible to outflow enumeration. Owner and receiver are
   protocol-stamped indexed topics. <strong>HIGH</strong> confidence marks a
   confirmed deposit&rarr;withdraw round-trip on a vault the wallet actually
   funded; <strong>MEDIUM</strong> means no deposit was observed &mdash;
   confirm the emitting vault is legitimate (an address-less query does not
   pre-verify it). Amounts are raw; leads are for review, NEVER a followed
   destination, and the recoverable total is unchanged.</em></p>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Owner (traced)</th>
      <th>Exit recipient</th>
      <th>Vault</th>
      <th>Assets (raw)</th>
      <th>Round-trip</th>
      <th>Confidence</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
  {% for ld in vault_leads.leads %}
    <tr>
      <td class="mono">{{ ld.owner | short_address(prefix=10, suffix=4) }}</td>
      <td class="mono">{{ ld.exit_recipient | short_address(prefix=10, suffix=4) }}</td>
      <td class="mono">{{ ld.vault | short_address(prefix=10, suffix=4) }}</td>
      <td class="mono">{{ ld.assets_raw }}</td>
      <td>{{ "yes" if ld.round_trip_confirmed else "no" }}</td>
      <td>{{ ld.confidence }}</td>
    </tr>
  {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>
{% endif %}

<footer class="brief-footer">
  <div class="footer-brand">Recupero · Investigation Services</div>
  <div class="footer-meta">
    <code>{{ investigation_id }}</code><br/>
    Generated {{ generated_at }} UTC · v{{ software_version }}<br/>
    <span class="confidential">Internal Use Only.</span>
    Not for distribution to issuers, exchanges, or law enforcement.
    For external-shareable artifacts see freeze_request_*.html and
    le_handoff_*.html in the same investigation folder.
  </div>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
